==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thermantidote
<hw>Ther*man"ti*dote</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ heat
+ E. <ets>antidote</ets>.]</ety> <def>A device for circulating and
cooling the air, consisting essentially of a kind of roasting fan fitted
in a window and incased in wet tatties.</def> <mark>[India]</mark></p>

<p><q>Will you bring me to book on the mountains, or where the
<qex>thermantidotes</qex> play?</q> <rj><qau>Kipling.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thermetograph</ent>⟦br⟧
